ly childhood can result in linguistic, creative and social advantages. The authors, all multilinguals themselves, parents of multilingual children, and researchers on language and multilingualism, aim to provide advice and inspiration for multilingual families across the world. The latest research on multilingualism and the authors’ own experiences are used to provide a friendly, accessible guide to raising and nurturing happy multilingual children.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aBilingualism in children. 0aChild development. 0aChild rearing. 0aLanguage acquisition. 7aPSYCHOLOGY / General.2bisacsh  aBilingualism.  aChild language acquisition.  aFamily.  aLanguage Development.  aLanguage acquisition of several languages.  aMultilingual family.  aMultilingualism.  aOPOL.  aOne parent one language.  aParenting.1 aDewaele, Jean-Marc, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aDewaele, Jean-Marc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFestman, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoarch, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPoarch, Gregory J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066312908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309758640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783097586423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783097586/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066312-9  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN 